703571f-b.title: Brooklyn: Clarendon Road - 59th Street (East)
703571f-b.text:
(1)
Clarendon Road, (formerly known as Canarsie Lane at this point),
south side, between Sast 59th Street and Ralph Ave., showing the Pieter
Claesen Wyckoff farmhouse, built in 1664.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Amnneeeter Cellection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2) The same; viewed from the opposite side.
1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Colleetion.

703573f-a.title: Brooklyn: Clarendon Road - 59th Street (East)
703573f-a.text:
(1)
Clarendon Road, north side, (formerly called Canarsie Lane at this
point), between East 59th Street and Ralph Ave., showing the north side
of the Albert Terhune Lott House, nearly opposite the Wyckoff House.
The house was occupied by John Lott in 1794, by Albert Terhune Lott,
between 1860 and 1873, and sold and vacated by the Lott family about
1903. In an upper room were found the Terhune family papers. This
house is no longer in existence.
About 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, from another angle.
About 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
